The second last example in **Whitespace** contains code snippets using the reserved word `class`:

``` Javascript
var leds = stage.selectAll('.led')
    .data(data)
  .enter().append('svg:svg')
    .class('led', true)
    .attr('width',  (radius + margin) * 2)
  .append('svg:g')
    .attr('transform', 'translate(' + (radius + margin) + ',' + (radius + margin) + ')')
    .call(tron.led);
```

This contradicts an earlier section, **Object**, which says:

> Use readable synonyms in place of reserved words.

``` Javascript
// bad
var superman = {
  class: 'alien'
};

// bad
var superman = {
  klass: 'alien'
};

// good
var superman = {
  type: 'alien'
};
```
